cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR

This paper discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) and machine learning (ML) techniques to optimize wireless local area networks (WLANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). ML techniques are also discussed, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category as well. The use of SDN implies a focus on control and management, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization and resource management, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
